A friend of mine who is a bushcrafter and often has slept in the open, survived off trapping small game, gathered, etc. said people tend to overestimate how dangerous wilderness is to their body and underestimate how dangerous cities, computers, etc. are to their devotional life.

It's far more likely for the roaring lion to devour your soul at home than wild dogs to tear your legs apart on a contemplative forest walk at night. Having access to the common psychic domain and its lack of boundaries is like sleeping with a poisonous snake next to your pillow.

Like you can imagine a Florentine 14th century short story about a fat woman hiring multiple painters to draw portraits of her from her best angle, make her seem as beautiful as possible, etc., looming over them physically while they are at work. Lindy in the eye of the beholder.

There is a very specific type of slightly older guy (like early to mid 30s) who has lots of personal stories involving driving at midnight and various women, e.g. having to pick some female friend from the airport and hitting a deer etc. who tends to be very reliable as a person.

Generally a very calm, moderate personality, but a beyond loyal friend. Tends to be somewhat disaffected with life and quietly disheartened for a few years and then gets married and makes a solid father afterwards. Enjoys to have a drink now and then. Very specific type of man.

I guess the driving women around at night part is because of a combination of high morals (would never take advantage of anyone) and being so responsible. Not to be too Lavaterian but if you know a guy like this never let him go as a friend and treasure him, he would die for you.

For the record I am very unlike this type of man, I tend to be unreliable, crude and obscure, never pick my phone, never do anything on time, cross boundaries, etc. If a girl comes to me it will be to ask me some unusual philosophical sage question. But this type of guy is golden

People like the flashier "girlfriend who is a tennis pro" conceptuals, but cataloguing the various types of reliable men who are trustworthy, upstanding, good-hearted, and overall the ones that keep civilization running is just as important. Friendship matters. Friends matter.
